- Used for health-checking of a server

* installing health check

- go to route53 console click on health checks
- create health check
- keep everything default except ip of server add ip of your own server
- create health check
- associate this healthcheck with the server
- go to a record edit and select the respective health check record to associate them with the particular web server
- if any of server goes down the status will be checked as unhealthy so all the traffic will be routed to the server which is healthy
